WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Maintaining some degree of website

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:05.000
accessibility is a legal requirement in

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.000
many countries, including the UK and USA.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:11.000
But more than that, it's about creating

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.000
more inclusive online spaces for everyone.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.000
The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:20.000
are designed to make content on

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:23.000
desktops, laptops, tablets,

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:26.000
and mobile devices more accessible to a

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.000
wider range of people, especially those

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
with disabilities, including

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.000
blindness and low vision,

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:35.000
deafness and hearing loss,

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:38.000
limited movement,

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:41.000
speech disabilities,

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.000
photosensitivity,

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:48.000
and some learning disabilities like dyslexia.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.000
The guidelines state that content and

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
user interfaces should be perceivable,

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.000
operable, understandable, robust,

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:57.000
and reliable. But what do these

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:00.000
principles mean in practice?

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Perceivable. Making your content

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
perceivable means improving visibility

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:10.000
and readability through clear and consistent
headers that enhance the user experience,

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:13.000
descriptive alt text for

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:19.000
images and considerations for screen readers.

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:22.000
Operable. An operable navigation

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:24.000
and user interface means users can

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:27.000
navigate with a keyboard alone,

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:30.000
without using a mouse or trackpad.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.000
They have time to read and interact

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:34.000
with your content,

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:37.000
understand their position on the page,

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:39.000
and easily move through your website,

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:41.000
finding all the information

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:44.000
they're looking for.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Understandable. It's important to make your
content and the user journey

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:51.000
as easy as possible to understand.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.000
Use clear and simple language,

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:55.000
be consistent throughout the

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:58.000
navigation and provide meaningful error
messages to minimize

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:01.000
confusion.

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:04.000
Robust and reliable. When
building robust and reliable websites,

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:06.000
it's important to ensure compatibility

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:08.000
with various browsers and assistive

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:10.000
technologies, allowing users to access

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:13.000
your content regardless of the tools

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:15.000
they use. This means both future-proofing

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:18.000
and iterating for the latest technology.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Once you understand these principles,

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.000
you can start to implement them by following

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.000
the Web Content Accessibility

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.000
Guidelines linked in the description.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:31.000
Then you can assess how well your site conforms.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:35.000
Level A is basic accessibility.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:39.000
Level AA is strong accessibility.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.000
Level AAA is excellent accessibility.

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:45.000
Level AA is the standard all

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:48.000
websites should be aiming for, while AAA

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:50.000
criteria are generally considered more

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:53.000
applicable to specific circumstances and

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:55.000
content types. It's unlikely you'll need

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.000
to tick every AAA box, but some may be

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:01.000
relevant to your business or users.

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:03.000
So next time you start a website project or

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:06.000
update your site, be sure to check

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.000
whether it meets user expectations and

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:11.000
accessibility guidelines, or get in touch

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:12.000
and we'll be happy to help.

